Task: Fully populate and functionalize all 13 sub-tabs within the "Environments" view.
​1. Data Simulation (The "Live" Feel):
​Pods & Nodes: Implement a useState hook with a useEffect interval. Every 3 seconds, randomly fluctuate CPU and RAM usage by \pm 2\%.
​Logic: If CPU usage > 90%, change the status badge to "Warning" (Yellow). If < 90%, keep it "Healthy" (Green pulsing dot).
​2. The Deployment Flow (Strict Logic):
​Sequential Selection: Create a state machine for the "New Deployment" form.
​Step 1: Pipeline (Options: Web, Worker, Cron)
​Step 2: Provider (Options: GitHub, Bitbucket, GitLab) — Disabled until Step 1 is chosen.
​Step 3: Repository (Fetch mock list) — Disabled until Step 2 is chosen.
​Step 4: Branch (Options: main, develop, staging) — Disabled until Step 3 is chosen.
​Error State: If GitHub is selected as Provider, show the specific alert: "No account connected. [Link GitHub Account]" (Link must be an OrangeLink).
​3. Missing Tabs Implementation:
​Firewall: Create a list of active rules. Add a button "Add My Current IP" that auto-populates the input with 192.168.1.1 (mock) and adds it to the list.
​Cache Warmer: Add a simple toggle switch for "Automatic Warming" and a "Clear All Cache" button that shows a success toast notification when clicked.
​Autoscaler: Add two slider inputs: "Minimum Pods" and "Maximum Pods." Show a live count of "Currently Active Pods."
​Diagnostics: Add a "Run Health Check" button. When clicked, show a terminal-style output window that prints: Checking SSL... OK, Checking DB Connection... OK, Checking Disk Space... 82%.
​4. Technical Consistency:
​Ensure every single ID (e.g., env-3029), Company name, and Website name uses the OrangeLink component.
​Use high-density tables (small padding) to fit more technical data on the screen, matching the "Developer Tool" aesthetic.
​Quick Actions Tab: Add big, clear buttons for: Restart PHP-FPM, Rebuild Containers, and Purge CDN.
​5. UI Transitions: > * Add a subtle "fade-in" animation when switching between tabs to prevent the UI from feeling "jumpy."
